            <bug_when>2012-01-04 11:47:50 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>On our staging host, the file export from a repository done with &#39;git archive&#39; 
exports unwanted files like .gitignore, .gitattributes and .svnauthors.txt, 
which are not meant to be in the SDK. This happens when the &#39;make -f 
Makefile.release release-sdk&#39; target is run.

The reason is an older version of git (1.5.6.5) on the staging host which does 
not support the &#39;export-ignore&#39; key (as in 1.7.0.4) in .gitattributes files.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
